We LOVE this place. The chicken is by far, much better than Pio Pio. Their service is fast, wait staff are polite. It's a cozy place. Definitely worth a try! ***************************************************************************  Edit: 10/21/17 - It disappoints me to write this review since we are regulars at this restaurant. However, tonight's dinner experience was a letdown.  As soon as we arrived, we realized why La Chacra has been closed for a minute. It turns out that they have gone through a brief renovation. The restaurant was packed, which meant the neighborhood has finally found our gem. Along with the new look, we also noticed they had new staff. There was a 20 minute wait, which ended being 45. We were seated in a small corner big enough for 4. Unfortunately, we had 6 people, but we made it work.  Our usual go-to order is the "Combo La Chacra" Which includes: Whole Chicken, Salad, Salchipapa, Maduros, Rice & Beans - all for $26.00. (Very good deal since the portions are generous.)  The wait for the food ended being around 25-30 minutes which is significantly longer than the usual wait time. But remember, it was a busy night. We understand.  The food tasted just as great tonight, as the many other nights that we dined in. The chicken was a little bit on the salty side Maybe it was over seasoned, but the the meat was still tender and juicy. We finished eating, and asked to pack our leftovers. We had a plateful of plantains, and fries and a ton of chicken left.  As the bill came, we noticed the total was more than the usual amount spent. After reviewing the receipt, we noticed we were charged for the "Super Combo" Which included TWO chickens, instead of one.  Here is a complete rundown of what the waitress told us, and their actions thereafter.  1. The waitress informed us that it was her mistake that they included an extra chicken in our order. But since it was included in our order.. she implied, it must be charged. 2. Since we asked to have our leftovers to go, we agreed to pay for the extra order of chicken. 3. She stated that we should've known it was 2 chicken, because there were 4 chicken wings on the plate. (not sure if we should've taken offense to her "lesson"?) 4. She would speak to her manager for a resolution. The waitress came back soon after, and gave us an amended receipt. 5. After we paid, we waited for our leftovers, but it turns out that they actually threw away our leftovers.  Basically, my point is that it was not our mistake that they gave us the wrong order. The waitress herself, admitted she made the mistake. Why sneak the charge on to our bill to cover their mistake, and hope that we don't notice? The proper way was to let us know they gave us the bigger combo.  I'm not sure if La Chacra is under new management, but we miss the old staff and their service! It saddens me to write this review about our local spot. We recommend them to our close friends and family. I would like to note that we were very patient and cordial about the whole situation. I'm leaving my 5 star rating because I hope tonight is just a wrinkle. The food is still excellent.

The combo meals are a great deal for families or groups. The owners are super nice too. Definitely go if you want real peruvian food. Dont go if you are expecting mexican food.

Peruvian food in Brooklyn. I've actually had better pollo (chicken) from another nearby Peruvian shop but what stands out here are the appetizers rather than the mains. Authentic real ceviches. I particularly liked the fish one. Nice amount of spicey kick, could use fewer onion slices and real roasted and poached corn kernals. Nice amount of flavor. The maduros and plantanos were good too. The main that stood out was the grilled skirt steak with fries and a fried egg. Tender and nice amount of char flavor that matched well with the rice and egg. Service to me could of been a bit better. They got our order wrong which delayed things and was a bit of a hassle getting them to get the right order in place. In the end though we did receive the right order.

Very shady business. They do not honor coupons or gift certificates, claiming BS conditions that contradicts what's written on the fine print. The coupon clearly says it can be used for takeout, but they say otherwise.  Friday night and the place had two small tables occupied. Yet they play games like this to turn away customers. I, for one, WILL NEVER come back to this place ever again. From the looks of it, it won't last long anyway.

I've ordered food from this place before. The chicken is hot, but the white meat is dry. I remember when they first opened, their chicken was very juicy. Now the meat is dry. Anyways, my review has to do with their service. It is very obvious that they are unprofessional and inexperienced with running a well-managed restaurant. One time, I went to the restaurant 12:30 to get an order of their chicken and the waitress (probably the owner) told me the chicken is not done yet. And that it was still roasting on the roaster. How can you expect to make money when you advertise you sell chicken and its NOT available???? The other day, I called for deliver. I ordered something very simple - their roast chicken! An hr later, I called back to inquire about my order that still didn't come yet. The person who picked up hung up on me. I called back again and this time the person who answered the phone told me that my order had not gotten to my house yet (merely blocks away from restaurant) bc they were very busy. I told them they should have told me that when I ordered that they were very busy and that I should expect to wait 1 hr for my food. Anyways, I told them I didn't want their food anymore. I will NEVER EVER be ordering or going to this place again bc there are so many OTHER food choices around and they clearly do not care about the customers.
the food simply delicious, We ate there once but we order food form that place once a week at least. Ceviche, avacado stuffed with chicken and potato salad something amazing.
